\begin_layout Section
Вариационное исчисление
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Необходимые условия экстремума
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Задача вариационного исчисления — поиск функций, доставляющих экстремум
 функционалу.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
F\left[y\right]=\intop L\left(y,y^{\prime},x\right)dx\to\min
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\delta F=F\left[y+\delta y\right]-F\left[y\right]=\intop\left[L\left(y+\delta y,y^{\prime}+\delta y^{\prime},x\right)-L\left(y,y^{\prime},x\right)\right]dx=\intop\left[\frac{\partial L}{\partial y}\delta y+\frac{\partial L}{\partial y^{\prime}}\delta y^{\prime}\right]dx+o\left(\delta y\right)
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\delta F=\intop\frac{\partial L}{\partial y}\delta ydx+\intop\frac{\partial L}{\partial y^{\prime}}\left(\delta y\right)^{\prime}dx
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Во втором интеграле произведём интегрирование по частям:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\delta F=\intop\frac{\partial L}{\partial y}\delta ydx+\left.\frac{\partial L}{\partial y^{\prime}}\delta y\right|-\intop\frac{d}{dx}\left(\frac{\partial L}{\partial y^{\prime}}\right)\delta ydx
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
На концах вариация равна нулю, поэтому:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\delta F=\intop\left[\frac{\partial L}{\partial y}-\frac{d}{dx}\left(\frac{\partial L}{\partial y^{\prime}}\right)\right]\delta ydx
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
В силу произвольности 
\begin_inset Formula $\delta y$
\end_inset

, получаем необходимые условия экстремума — уравнения Эйлера:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\frac{\partial L}{\partial y}=\frac{d}{dx}\left(\frac{\partial L}{\partial y^{\prime}}\right)
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Сохранение энергии
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Если 
\begin_inset Formula $L$
\end_inset

 не зависит явно от 
\begin_inset Formula $x$
\end_inset

 мы можем упростить:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\frac{dL}{dx}=\frac{\partial L}{\partial y}y^{\prime}+\frac{\partial L}{\partial y^{\prime}}\frac{dy^{\prime}}{dx}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
В силу уравнений Эйлера:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\frac{dL}{dx}=\frac{d}{dx}\left(\frac{\partial L}{\partial y^{\prime}}\right)y^{\prime}+\frac{\partial L}{\partial y^{\prime}}\frac{dy^{\prime}}{dx}=\frac{d}{dx}\left(\frac{\partial L}{\partial y^{\prime}}y^{\prime}\right)
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\frac{d}{dx}\left(\frac{\partial L}{\partial y^{\prime}}y^{\prime}-L\right)=0
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\frac{\partial L}{\partial y^{\prime}}y^{\prime}-L=const
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

